# Lessons Learned

Non-obvious things discovered while building this project. Newest at the top.

---

*2026-05-08* — Vercel env vars don't hot-reload in local dev

Spent 40 minutes wondering why a newly added `DATABASE_URL` wasn't being picked up. Turns out `vercel dev` caches env vars at startup — you have to restart the dev server after editing `.env.local`. The browser's auto-reload made it look like everything was refreshing, but the server process wasn't.

---

*2026-05-05* — Sandbox a scaffolding tool before releasing it

Ran the `pm-docs-init` skill against a fresh empty project before shipping it. That dry-run immediately exposed a design question (should `HANDOFF.md` be committed or gitignored?) that would have shipped as a silent wrong default for half the audience. Without the sandbox, the tension stays invisible until a real user hits it.

---
